At the time of this question Burbank, California is on a streak of 17 days with no rain, following a record storm and [flooding](https://www.foxweather.com/weather-news/southern-california-los-angeles-evacuations-severe-storms-flooding-burn-scars) of October 14, 2025. In June, July and August 2025, the city received no rain.  Please see history [here](https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/sites/monthlysum.php?station=BUR\&network=CA_ASOS).&#x20;

Southern California remains under drought, with Burbank (following the mid-October rains) considered under moderate drought ([D1](https://www.drought.gov/states/california)).&#x20;

